<paragraph blockId="15.[151,1437,259,1186]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,267,259,285]" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Diagnose.</emphasis>
A 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Vaillant" authorityYear="1976" box="[306,436,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Psychodidae" genus="Berdeniella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[306,436,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="52">Berdeniella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
-like species but with two large tenacula of unequal size arranged in line on epandrial appendages; thorax and wings without characteristics; gonostyli longer than gonocoxites and markedly thinner in distal half; lateral sclerites of aedeagus with sharp tips, inner sclerites broad with apical edge serrate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
